<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>The Summoner Druid is a very uncommon build as most Druids will end up focusing their skills in the Elemental or Shapeshifting Tree while only using Summons as support. That being said, if a player focuses all of their efforts into the Summoning Tree they can create a build that is effective enough to clear the game while being decently safe.</p>
<p>One of the hidden traits of the Druid Summoning Skill Tree is that Soft points (Points from +Skills on Items) actually improve Synergies for Skills as well as the main Skill. This only applies to the Druid Summoning Tree and no other Skill Tree in the game of Diablo 2. This makes getting and to Skills gear even more important for this character than most others.</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the Summon Druid. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2SummonGrizzly@@@ - Damage Synergy for your Summons, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2SummonDireWolf@@@ - Main skill used. Invest immediately, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2SummonSpiritWolf@@@ - Attack Rating and Defense for your summons, required</li>
</ol>

